data.value: Enter elements to be dynamically replaced. in the request. E.g.: Regex: Accept:(.+)$ Replacement: application/json will replace the value of the accept header with application/json

data.name: label10.Text
data.value:
Enter patterns to be updated dynamically in the request from responses or using custom functions.
For function type enter the functions separated by comma. Accepted values are ticks, base64encode, base64decode, urlencode, urldecode and increment.
Increment will simply increase the current value by one. You may need to track the value through a separate response pattern definition.
A value of 'ticks,base64encode,urlencode' will initialize the variable with the current time, base 64 encode it and then url encode the value.
If only base64 and url encode functions will be passed as parameters the current variable value extracted from the request.
